HEADWORD: Cerulein
<hw>Ce*ru"le*in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>caeruleus</ets> sky-blue.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A fast
dyestuff, <chform>C20H8O6</chform>, made by heating gallein with strong
sulphuric acid. It dyes mordanted fabrics green.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

